overview: An anthology series centering on different characters and locations, including a house with a murderous past, an insane asylum, a witch coven, a freak show, a haunted hotel, a possessed farmhouse, a cult, the apocalypse and a slasher camp.
name: American Horror Story

episodes.overview: A therapist and his family move across the country to escape their troubled past, but quickly discover that their new home comes with its own horrific baggage.
episodes.name: Pilot

episodes.overview: Vivien and Violet get themselves caught in a dangerous situation. Meanwhile, Ben goes back to Boston to fix a mistake that he made.
episodes.name: Home Invasion

episodes.overview: Vivien learns the horrific truth about the house's first residents and Ben's visitor causes him to further unravel about what really happened in the haunted house. Constance and Moira have their history revealed.
episodes.name: Murder House

episodes.overview: The line between the living and the dead blurs on Halloween. Two of the house's previous residents give the Harmons decorating advice.
episodes.name: Halloween (1)

episodes.overview: Tate comes face to face with his past, and Ben and Vivien are haunted by a new houseguest before Halloween night comes to an end.
episodes.name: Halloween (2)

episodes.overview: Constance enlists Violet's assistance with Tate. Ben helps a new patient confront his fears.
episodes.name: Piggy, Piggy

episodes.overview: Moira persuades a buyer to make an offer, while Constance and Larry work against her efforts.
episodes.name: Open House

episodes.overview: The man in the rubber suit is revealed.
episodes.name: Rubber Man

episodes.overview: One of history's most famous murder victims pays the house a visit. Constance discovers more of Tate's bad behavior.
episodes.name: Spooky Little Girl

episodes.overview: Violet learns about the rules of the house. The truth about Larry's condition is explained. Constance is interrogated by the police.
episodes.name: Smoldering Children

episodes.overview: Vivien gives birth. Tate and Violet attempt to rid the house of some of its ghosts for good.
episodes.name: Birth

episodes.overview: In the aftermath of family tragedy, Ben tries to take his child out of the Murder House. Meanwhile, Violet and Vivien accustom themselves to their new living arrangements, Constance raises Tate's child as her own and a new family buys the house.
episodes.name: Afterbirth

episodes.overview: Terrifying evils blur the boundaries between reality and insanity at the Briarcliff Manor.
episodes.name: Welcome to Briarcliff

episodes.overview: An exorcist is called to Briarcliff to help save a troubled farm boy; Sister Jude's darkest secret is revealed.
episodes.name: Tricks and Treats

episodes.overview: A violent storm allows a group of patients to plan a daring escape; Sister Jude is haunted by her past.
episodes.name: Nor'easter

episodes.gueststars: |Franka Potente|Fredric Lehne|John Lee Ames|Mark Consuelos|Matthew John Armstrong|
episodes.overview: A new patient exposes Arden's past; Kit learns why Grace was admitted to Briarcliff.
episodes.name: I Am Anne Frank (1)

episodes.overview: Sister Jude employs a renowned Nazi hunter to gather evidence against Arden; Kit makes a surprising confession; Bloody Face is unmasked.
episodes.name: I Am Anne Frank (2)

episodes.gueststars: |Bob Bancroft|Kasey Mahaffy|Kirk Bovill|Mark Consuelos|Nikki Hahn|Tara Holt|
episodes.overview: A mysterious little girl is abandoned at Briarcliff; the Monsignor makes a Faustian pact with Dr. Arden; the origin of Bloody Face is revealed.
episodes.name: The Origins of Monstrosity

episodes.gueststars: |Erin Allin O'Reilly|Frances Conroy|Fredric Lehne|Sean Patrick Thomas|William Mapother|
episodes.overview: Sister Mary Eunice is terrified to discover a dark angel at Briarcliff; Kit makes a bold move to be reunited with Grace.
episodes.name: Dark Cousin

episodes.overview: A murderous Santa wreaks havoc on Briarcliff; Sister Jude faces off with the devil; Arden has a shocking encounter in the death chute.
episodes.name: Unholy Night

episodes.overview: The Monsignor takes an unlikely convert under his wing; Lana secures a new piece of evidence that can exonerate Kit; Dr. Arden witnesses a miraculous return.
episodes.name: The Coat Hanger

episodes.overview: The Monsignor confronts the Devil; Dr. Arden’s experiments reach a shocking conclusion; Dr. Thredson facilitates a surprising reunion for Kit.
episodes.name: The Name Game

episodes.overview: Grace tells Kit devastating news about Alma; Dr. Thredson receives an unexpected visitor; the Monsignor goes to extreme lengths to silence Jude.
episodes.name: Spilt Milk

episodes.overview: A deadly new inmate threatens Sister Jude's chance of release; Grace's obsession with the aliens turns violent.
episodes.name: Continuum

episodes.overview: Johnny sets out to complete his father's work; Lana leads the charge to finally shut down Briarcliff.
episodes.name: Madness Ends

episodes.overview: A young girl discovers she possesses a strange genetic affliction tracing back to the dark days of Salem; Fiona Goode returns to town.
episodes.name: Bitchcraft

episodes.overview: Fiona helps Zoe and Madison deal with a horrible tragedy; Delphine LaLaurie struggles to adjust to modern life; Cordelia faces a dark decision about her family.
episodes.name: Boy Parts

episodes.overview: Fiona takes on an unlikely protégé; a guilt-ridden Zoe tries to give Kyle his old life back; Madison has a fiery exchange with Joan Ramsey.
episodes.name: The Replacements

episodes.overview: Fiona's choices rattle a decades-long truce between the Salem witches and Marie Laveau; the Council of Witchcraft pays a surprise visit to the academy with disturbing allegations.
episodes.name: Fearful Pranks Ensue

episodes.overview: Besieged by Marie Laveau's army, Zoe unleashes a new power; Fiona and Myrtle clash over control of the coven; Madame LaLaurie is confronted by old ghosts.
episodes.name: Burn, Witch. Burn!

episodes.overview: Zoe, Queenie and Nan make contact with a dark spirit trapped in the academy; Cordelia's new power brings on a heartbreaking revelation.
episodes.name: The Axeman Cometh

episodes.overview: Fiona finds purpose in a dangerous love affair; Queenie questions her place in the Coven; Cordelia makes a decision about her mother.
episodes.name: The Dead

episodes.overview: Cordelia rallies the girls in the fight to stop Fiona; a dangerous new enemy puts Misty in the cross hairs; the rivalry between Marie Laveau and Delphine comes to a head.
episodes.name: The Sacred Taking

episodes.overview: Cordelia’s attacker is revealed. Fiona looks to form an alliance with Marie Laveau. Nan learns a disturbing truth about Luke’s past.
episodes.name: Head

episodes.overview: Fiona attempts to out the new supreme with a visit from Stevie Nicks; Cordelia learns the truth about Hank and the witch hunters; Madison tries to eliminate her competition for the supremacy.
episodes.name: The Magical Delights of Stevie Nicks

episodes.overview: Fiona and Laveau have a deadly face off with The Corporation; Cordelia makes a desperate sacrifice.
episodes.name: Protect the Coven

episodes.overview: Cordelia's latest vision puts the coven's future in question; the girls manifest powerful new gifts; Queenie's search for Marie Laveau leads her to hell and back.
episodes.name: Go to Hell

episodes.overview: A new Supreme rises.
episodes.name: The Seven Wonders

episodes.overview: One of the only surviving sideshows in the country struggles to stay in business during the dawning era of television; police make a terrifying discovery at a local farmhouse.
episodes.name: Monsters Among Us

episodes.overview: A citywide curfew threatens to shut down the freak show; a strongman from Ethel's troubled past arrives at camp; Gloria arranges a terrifying play date for Dandy; the Tattler Twins reveal a talent that could knock Elsa from the spotlight.
episodes.name: Massacres and Matinees

episodes.overview: The freaks refuse to perform on Halloween due to an old carny superstition; Jimmy is smitten by a woman claiming to be a fortuneteller; Ethel receives life-changing news.
episodes.name: Edward Mordrake (1)

episodes.overview: Edward Mordrake continues his search for a Freak to add to his ghostly coterie; Elsa tells the grisly story of her days in Germany; Jimmy and Maggie have a run-in with the Twisted Clown.
episodes.name: Edward Mordrake (2)

episodes.overview: Stanley and Maggie hatch a plan to murder the Freaks; Gloria hides the evidence of Dandy's gruesome new hobby; a health scare reveals Desiree may not be the oddity she once thought.
episodes.name: Pink Cupcakes

episodes.overview: Elsa unveils a dangerous new act; Stanley puts pressure on Maggie to murder Jimmy; Paul indulges in a secret romance.
episodes.name: Bullseye

episodes.overview: The women of the Freak Show rally against Dell after his latest act of violence; a strange encounter with Dandy raises Jimmy’s suspicion about the clown murders.
episodes.name: Test of Strength

episodes.overview: Recent disappearances around camp raise Ethel’s suspicion of Elsa; Gloria makes a last ditch effort to contain Dandy’s bloodlust.
episodes.name: Blood Bath

episodes.overview: In the wake of a tragic loss, Jimmy sinks into a drunken despair; a reading from Maggie spurs Dandy to action; Stanley and Elsa track down the Twins.
episodes.name: Tupperware Party Massacre

episodes.overview: The death of a Freak sparks troubling behavior in Pepper; Elsa reveals the history of the Freak Show; Desiree grows suspicious of Maggie.
episodes.name: Orphans

episodes.overview: Elsa prepares for her move to Hollywood; the Twins grow enamored with a traveling salesman; Dell plots Jimmy’s escape from police custody.
episodes.name: Magical Thinking

episodes.overview: Maggie tries to prove her loyalty to Jimmy; Meanwhile, the Twins receive troubling information about Chester.
episodes.name: Show Stoppers

episodes.overview: The Freaks rebel against new management; Dandy prepares for his debut performance; Elsa arrives in Tinseltown.
episodes.name: Curtain Call

episodes.overview: Detective and family man John Lowe investigates a chain of gruesome murders in Los Angeles. A mysterious tip points him to the enigmatic Hotel Cortez.
episodes.name: Checking In

episodes.overview: Fashion mogul Will Drake brings couture to the Hotel Cortez. A model catches The Countess' eye. John learns about the hotel's sadistic first owner.
episodes.name: Chutes and Ladders

episodes.overview: Alex is pushed to her breaking point after Scarlett stirs up memories of Holden. Donovan is targeted by a dangerous rival of The Countess.
episodes.name: Mommy

episodes.overview: John receives an invitation to attend an exclusive Devil's Night soirée. Alex tries to diagnose Holden's strange condition.
episodes.name: Devil's Night

episodes.overview: Alex uses an unconventional treatment to save a dying patient. A Halloween-hating couple tests Iris’s limits.
episodes.name: Room Service

episodes.overview: Ramona and Donovan enact their plan for revenge. Liz Taylor finds true love. The resident of Room 33 is revealed.
episodes.name: Room 33

episodes.overview: Will Drake’s renovations uncover one of the Hotel’s greatest secrets. John undergoes psychiatric evaluation. The Countess learns the fate of her first love.
episodes.name: Flicker

episodes.overview: John closes in on The Ten Commandments Killer. Sally’s arrangement with March is revealed.
episodes.name: The Ten Commandments Killer

episodes.overview: The Countess is reunited with her one true love. Donovan and Ramona take another stab at revenge. A careless decision lands Alex in hot water.
episodes.name: She Wants Revenge

episodes.overview: Alex enlists John's help to contain an outbreak. Donovan learns the Countess' true intentions. Liz and Iris plan to leave the hotel for good.
episodes.name: She Gets Revenge

episodes.overview: Ramona draws vitality from an unlikely source. Sally uses her past to negotiate her future. Scarlett learns the truth of her family’s affliction.
episodes.name: Battle Royale

episodes.overview: Iris and Liz oversee a new era at the Cortez. John and Alex struggle to adapt to life outside the hotel.
episodes.name: Be Our Guest

episodes.overview: Matt and Shelby, an interracial couple, decide to move to North Carolina and get away from the big city for peace and quiet and to start a new life, until Shelby starts seeing strange things that haunt her day and night.
episodes.name: Chapter 1

episodes.overview: Matt and Shelby find a revealing videotape in a hidden cellar. Meanwhile, Lee's daughter Flora makes a new friend, and the mysterious events continue.
episodes.name: Chapter 2

episodes.overview: Nightmares become an inescapable reality as unique stories of people's lives in America reveal the astonishing power of the supernatural.
episodes.name: Chapter 3

episodes.overview: Scathach presents herself for the first time and reveals what she wants. However, Tomasyn and the ghost settlers have other plans.
episodes.name: Chapter 4

episodes.overview: The Millers attempt to escape the house with the help of an unexpected ally.
episodes.name: Chapter 5

episodes.overview: The producer of My Roanoke Nightmare decides to follow up his huge hit with a second season... putting the actors and their real-life counterparts in the same house during the Blood Moon, and seeing if Lee confesses to Mason's murder.
episodes.name: Chapter 6

episodes.overview: Chaos breaks out at the house as Audrey, Monet, and Lee try to escape through the secret tunnel. Meanwhile, Shelby learns why Matt came back to the house, and Agnes considers a career change.
episodes.name: Chapter 7

episodes.overview: Lee, Audrey, and Monet try to escape the Polks. Meanwhile, Shelby and Dominic are trapped by the ghosts in the house.
episodes.name: Chapter 8

episodes.overview: Three My Roanoke Nightmare fans pay a visit to the House, unaware that they've arrived at the worst possible time. Meanwhile, Lee and Audrey try to recover the camera, and a new visitor doesn't prove very helpful.
episodes.name: Chapter 9

episodes.overview: Season finale.  Lana Winters is interviewing Lee Harris about what happened during the Return to Roanoke.
episodes.name: Chapter 10

episodes.overview: After Trump is elected President, Ally Mayfair-Richards is beset by all of her old phobias... and they appear to be coming to life.
episodes.name: Election Night

episodes.overview: Ally, Ivy and Oz meet the new neighbors. Kai runs for city council. Detective Samuels investigates a murder. A blackout terrorizes Ally.
episodes.name: Don't Be Afraid of the Dark

episodes.overview: The community turns on Ally after she shoots and kills a Hispanic man. At home tensions between Ally and Ivy grow worse, and Kai may be Ally's only hope.
episodes.name: Neighbors from Hell

episodes.overview: Kai gathers familiar faces to join his cult as the events surrounding 11/8/16 are explored.
Beverly's journalistic integrity is called into question; Kai plans to broadcast a gruesome murder committed by the cult; Ally's phobias reach a new low
episodes.name: Holes

episodes.overview: Ally takes Meadow to Rudy in the hopes that she will confirm her story about the cult. Meanwhile, an unexpected opponent runs against Kai in the city council election.
episodes.name: Mid-Western Assassin

episodes.overview: Kai begins to solidify his grasp on power after winning the election, and a mysterious woman warns Beverly, Ivy, and Winter that Kai will soon cast them aside.
episodes.name: Valerie Solanas Died for Your Sins: Scumbag

episodes.overview: Ally confronts Kai. Meanwhile, Winter must choose between Kai and Beverly when he makes a questionable decision.
episodes.name: Winter of Our Discontent

episodes.overview: Kai seeks to test the loyalty of his cult. Ally seeks revenge. Oz learns about his parentage.
episodes.name: Drink the Kool-Aid

episodes.overview: Kai receives visits from Charles Manson as he begins to question everyone around him.
episodes.name: Charles (Manson) in Charge

episodes.overview: The FBI arrest Kai, but he continues to amass power in prison. Meanwhile, Ally tries to move on with her life but decides to go into politics.
episodes.name: Great Again

episodes.overview: In the wake of the nuclear apocalypse, a select group survives in a sealed bunker dubbed Outpost Three ruled by a tyrannical matriarch. As tensions rise, the occupants question whether the real hell is outside... or locked in with them.
episodes.name: The End

episodes.gueststars: |Ash Santos|Chris Ferro|Erika Ervin|Jason Michael Snow|Jeffrey Bowyer-Chapman|Joan Collins|Kyle Allen|Navaris Darson|Riley Schmidt|
episodes.overview: A new occupant arrives at the Outpost with alarming news, causing a domino effect of lust, betrayal, and self-destruction. Langdon meets the survivors for an inquisition. Strange signs herald something coming. Lovers unite, and loved ones turn on one another. Blood reveals mysterious truths.
episodes.name: The Morning After

episodes.overview: As Ms. Mead grapples with her identity, Michael reveals more of his. Coco’s ex rears his ugly head. When a carriage with a box of apples arrive, Venable crafts a plan to give the residents of Outpost 3 one magical night. Three guests crash the afterparty.
episodes.name: Forbidden Fruit

episodes.gueststars: |BD Wong|Billy Porter|Brendan McCarthy|Corey Clifford|David Atkinson|Frances Conroy|Gabourey Sidibe|Guido Cocomello|Janell Winkler|Jon Jon Briones|Kai Caster|Nathan Hurd|Ryan Fisher|Shaun Ross|Taissa Farmiga|Tom Lommel|
episodes.overview: Three years before the bombs drop, Outpost Three houses the Hawthorne School for Exceptional Young Men. Its inhabitants, warlocks living in the shadow of Cordelia Goode's coven, place their hopes on a new, troubled apprentice - Michael Langdon.
episodes.name: Could It Be... Satan?

episodes.gueststars: |Addie Chandler|BD Wong|Billy Porter|Frances Conroy|Gabourey Sidibe|John Getz|Jon Jon Briones|Lily Rabe|Mia Vavasseur|Sarah Finley|Stevie Nicks (Herself)|Taissa Farmiga|Wayne Pére|Zachary Read|
episodes.overview: Beset by visions of a terrifying future, Cordelia lets Michael attempt the Seven Wonders. A wealthy new student joins the coven. John Henry's suspicions are short lived. Michael's test brings back a familiar face along with a chorus of warnings.
episodes.name: Boy Wonder

episodes.gueststars: |Billy Porter|Carlo Rota|Cassidy Naber|Celia Finkelstein|Connie Britton|Dylan McDermott|Emily Mest|Frances Conroy|Irene Roseen|Jennifer Jalene|Jessica Lange|John Duerler|Mena Suvari|Naomi Grossman|Raina Matheson|Sam Kinsey|Scarlett Fernandez|Stacy Highsmith|Taissa Farmiga|
episodes.overview: Behold and Madison are sent on a mission to Murder House to uncover the truth about Michael Langdon’s past. Although revelations about their next Supreme paint a bleak picture—there may be room to set some things right.
episodes.name: Return to Murder House

episodes.gueststars: |BD Wong|Billy Porter|Carrick O'Quinn|Frances Conroy|Gabourey Sidibe|Jamie Brewer|Joan Collins|Joe Lorenzo|John Venable|Jon Jon Briones|Josh Plasse|Kevin Foster|Lance Reddick|Lansoul the Pale Horse|Lauren Stamile|Mariah Fairclough|Nathan Hurd|Robert Loftin|Shaun Ross|Taissa Farmiga|Tom Fitzpatrick|Violet Hicks|
episodes.overview: The witches recruit a clairvoyant friend to expose deceivers in their midst. Cordelia looks to make a deal with another sort of devil. A test of Mallory's powers reveal more about the Supreme-elect. Covens unite to send Michael a fiery message.
episodes.name: Traitor

episodes.gueststars: |Alman Bilal|Billy Eichner|Carlo Rota|Cole Stratton|Dominic Burgess|Garrett Westton|Gloria Laino|Harriet Sansom Harris|J.T. Sherwood|Jim Deangelo|Kingston Foster|Lauren Mungo|Megan Davis|Rachael Drummond|Roger Hewlett|Sandra Bernhard|Tice Proctor|
episodes.overview: After the death of his most trusted advisors, Michael goes on a vision quest to find his place in the world. A group of followers devoted to his unholy father point him toward his destiny.
episodes.name: Sojourn

episodes.overview: Lamenting the state of society, Mutt and Jeff set their sights on a "brighter" future. An emboldened Michael plummets the Coven into their darkest hour, forcing them to gamble their hopes on the abilities of one witch.
episodes.name: Fire and Reign

episodes.overview: The witches prepare for a final epic battle with Michael Langdon. An old face returns to help with the plan.
episodes.name: Apocalypse Then

episodes.overview: In the summer of 1984, five friends escape Los Angeles to work as counselors at Camp Redwood. As they adjust to their new jobs, they quickly learn that the only thing scarier than campfire tales is the past coming to haunt you.
episodes.name: Camp Redwood

episodes.overview: Darkness descends upon the camp. Although it's lights out, evil has no curfew.
episodes.name: Mr. Jingles

episodes.overview: Imitation is the best form of tragedy. Coming clean can be pretty messy.
episodes.name: Slashdance

episodes.overview: Mr. Jingles closes in on the one who got away as the counselors rally to escape Camp Redwood.
episodes.name: True Killers

episodes.overview: As twilight broaches, the survivors brace for a final brawl.
episodes.name: Red Dawn

episodes.overview: With the horrors of the night behind them the survivors deal with the fallout of their choices.
episodes.name: Episode 100

episodes.overview: A hidden chapter of Camp Redwood is revealed. The survivors help a stranded hitchhiker.
episodes.name: The Lady in White

episodes.overview: A deadly trio emerges, hell-bent on unleashing a new era at Camp Redwood. Our former counselors desperately try to keep history from repeating itself.
episodes.name: Rest in Pieces

episodes.overview: Camp Redwood draws in a lost soul looking for closure.
episodes.name: Final Girl
